# Everything in this folder is consumed on macOS. Keep LF line endings in the
# working tree regardless of the checkout platform.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: this repo is authored on Windows with
# core.autocrlf=true, which rewrites text files to CRLF in the working tree. If
# make-terminal-app-profile.sh reaches a Mac with CRLF endings - by being copied
# or zipped from a Windows working tree rather than cloned - it fails with:
#     zsh: ./make-terminal-app-profile.sh: bad interpreter: /bin/bash^M
# which reads as "the script is broken" rather than "the line endings are wrong".
# `eol=lf` pins the working-tree ending on every platform and prevents that.
#
# Scoped to this folder on purpose: it cannot affect the Windows side of the
# repo (install.ps1, the Windows Terminal scheme, FancyZones layouts).

*.sh          text eol=lf
*.toml        text eol=lf
*.lua         text eol=lf
*.conf        text eol=lf
*.md          text eol=lf
*.ghostty     text eol=lf
*.itermcolors text eol=lf
